claim.claim-text:
1. A method for conveying data card information, comprising:
associating at least one of a bar code reader or a magnetic stripe detector with a data conveyance device;
associating at least one of a bar code emulator or a magnetic stripe emulator with said data conveyance device;
obtaining a plurality of data card information sets, each data card information set of said plurality of data card information sets corresponding to a respective data card of a plurality of data cards, each data card of said plurality of data cards corresponding to a respective entity of a plurality of entities;
storing on said data conveyance device said plurality of data card information sets;
using at least one of said bar code reader or said magnetic stripe detector associated with said data conveyance device to identify a first entity of said plurality of entities; and
using at least one of said bar code emulator or said magnetic stripe emulator associated with said data conveyance device to convey a first data card information set corresponding to said first entity.

17. The system of claim 8, wherein said first data conveyance device comprises:
a first light conduit having a first opening at a first end, a second opening at a second end opposite said first end, and a side opening between said first opening and said second opening;
a first light source, said first light source configured for outputting a first light that initially enters said first light conduit through said side opening, reflects off said first light conduit, and exits said first light conduit through said first opening;
a first detector for detecting a second light exiting said second opening; and
a first processor interfaced with said first detector, said first processor configured for conveying data based on at least one of said first light or said second light.
